- Install Elasticsearch module via npm: `npm install @nestjs/elasticsearch`
- Use the latest version of NestJS and Elasticsearch.
- Configure the ElasticsearchModule in your app.module.ts:
```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [
    ElasticsearchModule.register({
      node: 'http://localhost:9200',
    }),
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```
- To index data, use `ElasticsearchService`:
```typescript
this.elasticsearchService.index({ index: 'my-index', body: { title: 'test' } });
```
- For searching, use the `search` method:
```typescript
const result = await this.elasticsearchService.search({
  index: 'my-index',
  body: {
    query: {
      match: { title: 'test' },
    },
  },
});
```
- Key config options include `node`, `username`, and `password`.
- For maintaining data synchronization, consider using NestJS's event-driven architecture to trigger reindexing on entity updates.

